{"id":479647,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rocky_Bridges","text":"Everett Lamar \"Rocky\" Bridges (August 7, 1927 \u2013 January 27, 2015) was an American baseball utility infielder. He played in Major League Baseball from 1951 to 1961. He played for the Brooklyn Dodgers, Cincinnati Reds, and St. Louis Cardinals of the National League. He also played for the Washington Senators, Detroit Tigers, Cleveland Indians, and Los Angeles Angels of the American League.\nBridges was born in Refugio, Texas. He was married to Mary who died in 2008 and had four children.\nBridges died on January 27, 2015 in Coeur d'Alene, Idaho, aged 87.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Americans","surface_form":"American","offset":73},{"uri":"Baseball","surface_form":"baseball","offset":82},{"uri":"Utility_infielder","surface_form":"utility infielder","offset":91},{"uri":"Major_League_Baseball","surface_form":"Major League Baseball","offset":123},{"uri":"Brooklyn_Dodgers","surface_form":"Brooklyn Dodgers","offset":182},{"uri":"Cincinnati_Reds","surface_form":"Cincinnati Reds","offset":200},{"uri":"St._Louis_Cardinals","surface_form":"St. Louis Cardinals","offset":221},{"uri":"National_League","surface_form":"National League","offset":248},{"uri":"History_of_the_Washington_Senators_(1901%E2%80%9360)","surface_form":"Washington Senators","offset":288},{"uri":"Detroit_Tigers","surface_form":"Detroit Tigers","offset":309},{"uri":"Cleveland_Indians","surface_form":"Cleveland Indians","offset":325},{"uri":"Los_Angeles_Angels_of_Anaheim","surface_form":"Los Angeles Angels","offset":348},{"uri":"American_League","surface_form":"American League","offset":374},{"uri":"Refugio%2C_Texas","surface_form":"Refugio","offset":411},{"uri":"Texas","surface_form":"Texas","offset":420},{"uri":"Coeur_d%27Alene%2C_Idaho","surface_form":"Coeur d'Alene","offset":526},{"uri":"Idaho","surface_form":"Idaho","offset":541}]}